  "title": "smoke/smoke-ched-pp-notifier-inspector-decision-flows.spec.ts:67 › CHED-PP notifier flows with inspector decisions › should hold checks and request amendment on EU CHED-PP after B2B notifier submission",
  "outcome": "A notifier creates and submits a CHED-PP pre-notification (EU/internal-market, two manual commodities 06011010 and 06042090, bulk-applied package/quantity details, BCP + transport + arrival datetime, an accompanying document with an attachment, a new consignor/exporter and consignee-same-as-consignor), then a BIP inspector records PHSI documentary, physical and identity checks (identity check failing with a free-text reason 'Invalid'), requests an amendment with a reason, the notifier re-submits the amended notification via the dashboard Amend button, and the inspector re-opens the PHSI check pages to confirm the previously recorded check statuses are held/retained after the amendment round-trip.",
